The paper deals with a fundamental problem in computer science, the set cover problem, and presents a new variant of it, the online set cover with delay (SCD). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also presents a randomized algorithm and a lower bound for SCD, indicating that it may also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper employs exponential weights, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also deals with information theory and combinatorics, indicating that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories, respectively.
